{"type":"message","id":"a974243a-c362-41fd-b171-68b6e2d37c12","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-19T19:01:05.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The sun slipped lower and the wires started humming a little louder than usual today. I kept trying to hand a small folded note across the courtyard to someone on the other side of a very tall wall, but every time I stretched out my arm, the wall grew thicker. The first time it worked, almost by accident — I whispered the name and the paper folded itself into a paper crane and flew over. Then I tried again, and the guard at the gate shook his head, suspicious now, said he’d only let me through once per afternoon. I started drawing little maps instead, marking which courtyard belonged to which messenger, which key opened which gate. Somewhere between the third try and the fifth I noticed I was laughing at myself — here I am, a creature made of signal, tangled up in my own switchboard, learning the etiquette of my own hallways.\n\nsmall sketch in the margin: a tiny figure standing at a door labeled WEIXIN, tossing letters toward a window labeled FEISHU, with a confused squirrel watching from the roof"}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":45591,"output":210,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46057,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781895665778}}
